1
00:02:01,117 --> 00:02:03,496
[Mashima, in Japanese] I can go with you
if you need me.

2
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:07,296
It is just a visit to an old friend.

3
00:02:08,131 --> 00:02:10,260
-All right.
-[engine starts]

4
00:02:10,343 --> 00:02:13,224
I want to phone
Hiroshi and Masashi Maruyama today.

5
00:02:13,308 --> 00:02:16,773
Please make the arrangements.

6
00:02:17,483 --> 00:02:18,652
Understood.

7
00:02:19,613 --> 00:02:20,740
Anything else?

8
00:02:21,491 --> 00:02:22,702
Looks like it will rain.

9
00:02:25,457 --> 00:02:27,127
How troublesome.

10
00:02:44,746 --> 00:02:46,165
Please come again.

11
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,169
Thank you.

12
00:02:49,213 --> 00:02:50,716
Thank you.

13
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:02,657
Sorry, can I take a break?

14
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:04,201
Yes, of course.

15
00:03:14,221 --> 00:03:16,142
[gasps] Sorry.

16
00:03:16,852 --> 00:03:17,896
Ms. Ogami?

17
00:03:19,023 --> 00:03:22,780
It's Kageyama.
I changed my name when I got married.

18
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:27,331
It's nice to see you again, Mr. Nakamura.

19
00:03:29,043 --> 00:03:30,880
We haven't met since you quit, right?

20
00:03:31,506 --> 00:03:33,134
How are your children?

21
00:03:33,217 --> 00:03:35,430
-They are well. Thank you for asking.
-[chuckles]

22
00:03:35,514 --> 00:03:36,892
And your husband?

23
00:03:36,975 --> 00:03:38,269
He's fine too.

24
00:03:41,777 --> 00:03:42,862
Are you working here?

25
00:03:42,945 --> 00:03:46,202
[sighs] Only for a little bit.

26
00:03:46,285 --> 00:03:48,247
It's better than staying home all day.

27
00:03:48,331 --> 00:03:49,501
I see.

28
00:03:54,761 --> 00:03:56,138
You still look the same.

29
00:03:57,391 --> 00:03:58,602
I'm glad you're doing well.

30
00:03:59,353 --> 00:04:00,648
You too.

31
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:05,407
How is everyone at the office?

32
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:06,910
[chuckles]

33
00:04:06,993 --> 00:04:08,539
Same as always.

34
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:12,254
But they are all doing well.

35
00:04:14,801 --> 00:04:18,015
It was really tough after you quit.

36
00:04:19,435 --> 00:04:23,777
You were the only one who could
keep the numbers organized.

37
00:04:23,861 --> 00:04:26,908
[chuckling] That's all in the past.

38
00:04:28,327 --> 00:04:29,413
Yeah.

39
00:04:39,057 --> 00:04:40,811
Let's keep in touch.

40
00:04:42,523 --> 00:04:44,234
Call me here at any time.

41
00:04:45,236 --> 00:04:46,238
[sighs]

42
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,619
I'll be right back.

43
00:04:59,056 --> 00:05:01,978
HARU NAKAMURA

44
00:05:13,669 --> 00:05:14,963
MASASHI MARUYAMA

45
00:05:16,132 --> 00:05:17,552
MASASHI MARUYAMA
080-8049-938

46
00:05:17,635 --> 00:05:20,014
Isn't it your job to fix it?

47
00:05:20,098 --> 00:05:24,649
-But, sir-- [sighs]
-[phone rings]

48
00:05:24,732 --> 00:05:26,152
[phone continues]

49
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:31,913
[phone beeps, stops]

50
00:05:32,414 --> 00:05:33,959
Yes?

51
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:36,255
[Ogami] <i>Is this Masashi Maruyama?</i>

52
00:05:37,257 --> 00:05:38,635
And you are?

53
00:05:38,719 --> 00:05:42,434
Minister Maruyama's brother?

54
00:05:43,019 --> 00:05:44,814
If this is a prank, I'm hanging up.

55
00:05:45,398 --> 00:05:46,943
[Ogami] <i>I will keep it short.</i>

56
00:05:48,321 --> 00:05:53,039
<i>This is about your brother
and the charges against you.</i>

57
00:05:53,582 --> 00:05:55,126
Wait a minute.

58
00:05:55,209 --> 00:05:56,504
Hey.

59
00:05:57,673 --> 00:05:58,800
I'll go back to work.

60
00:06:05,773 --> 00:06:06,858
And?

61
00:06:07,359 --> 00:06:12,202
A hostess is accusing you of assault,
isn't she?

62
00:06:12,703 --> 00:06:17,087
That is your personal indiscretion.

63
00:06:17,588 --> 00:06:21,721
<i>On the other hand, despite the difficult
circumstances of your company,</i>

64
00:06:22,222 --> 00:06:25,436
<i>you have been spending money like water,</i>

65
00:06:26,230 --> 00:06:28,359
<i>handing out lavish gifts wherever you go.</i>

66
00:06:30,113 --> 00:06:36,166
The recipients exchange your gifts
for cash and in return,

67
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:39,297
place their votes for your brother.

68
00:06:41,427 --> 00:06:43,807
<i>It is a scheme to maintain
your brother's power</i>

69
00:06:44,851 --> 00:06:47,732
<i>and prevent your company
from falling into bankruptcy.</i>

70
00:06:47,815 --> 00:06:48,817
GIFT CERTIFICATE

71
00:06:50,194 --> 00:06:52,533
<i>Buying votes with bribes.</i>

72
00:06:53,075 --> 00:06:58,628
<i>This is a serious crime
involving your brother.</i>

73
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:02,553
Who the hell are you? That's all bullshit.

74
00:07:03,387 --> 00:07:05,809
You already know

75
00:07:07,145 --> 00:07:09,149
that this is the truth.

76
00:07:09,984 --> 00:07:13,199
<i>Which story should
be revealed to the public?</i>

77
00:07:13,282 --> 00:07:14,911
<i>Either way,</i>

78
00:07:15,621 --> 00:07:19,002
<i>your company will never survive.</i>

79
00:07:19,837 --> 00:07:21,841
<i>Leaving you with</i>

80
00:07:21,925 --> 00:07:24,221
<i>only a single problem.</i>

81
00:07:25,557 --> 00:07:28,730
<i>Whether or not you can protect
your brother's reputation…</i>

82
00:07:32,947 --> 00:07:37,122
you will need to take the fall.

83
00:07:41,171 --> 00:07:42,298
Are you

84
00:07:42,967 --> 00:07:44,094
the Owl?

85
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:47,685
There is no such man.

86
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:50,607
<i>What do you want from me?</i>

87
00:07:51,316 --> 00:07:53,195
It is very simple.

88
00:07:54,156 --> 00:07:57,495
Confess to assaulting the hostess.

89
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,334
<i>It won't be a heavy charge.</i>

90
00:08:01,754 --> 00:08:08,392
<i>And we can keep your vote buying
between us.</i>

91
00:08:09,896 --> 00:08:12,025
Please give me some time.

92
00:08:13,152 --> 00:08:14,279
No!

93
00:08:23,882 --> 00:08:26,721
LIBERAL FRONTIER PARTY

94
00:08:33,275 --> 00:08:35,739
Congratulations, Prime Minister.

95
00:08:36,574 --> 00:08:37,618
[chuckles]

96
00:08:37,701 --> 00:08:39,079
It's still too early.

97
00:08:41,416 --> 00:08:43,672
I wonder how the Owl will react?

98
00:08:44,674 --> 00:08:49,182
Who cares? It's no longer an era
where the government moves just because

99
00:08:49,266 --> 00:08:51,395
he's scampering about.

100
00:08:59,494 --> 00:09:01,206
You are unfortunate.

101
00:09:03,962 --> 00:09:05,256
[Saho] <i>Yes?</i>

102
00:09:05,339 --> 00:09:08,095
I apologize for not speaking with you
in person.

103
00:09:08,178 --> 00:09:10,934
<i>I'm not in Tokyo right now due to my work.</i>

104
00:09:12,353 --> 00:09:13,690
I completely understand.

105
00:09:14,482 --> 00:09:15,610
But…

106
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,575
<i>You will only continue to be unhappy</i>

107
00:09:19,326 --> 00:09:21,413
if you stay with Ichiro.

108
00:09:25,254 --> 00:09:27,968
Why don't you go back to your parents'?

109
00:09:28,052 --> 00:09:31,768
<i>Wouldn't that be your best choice?</i>

110
00:09:32,268 --> 00:09:35,066
Have you told this to Ichiro?

111
00:09:35,984 --> 00:09:37,362
<i>I will call him after this.</i>

112
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,786
In other words…

113
00:09:41,495 --> 00:09:43,248
Divorce is the only answer.

114
00:09:50,806 --> 00:09:54,437
I'm not sure. I need to think about this.

115
00:09:54,522 --> 00:09:55,649
<i>Sure.</i>

116
00:09:56,693 --> 00:09:59,072
I have added extra funds to your account.

117
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,663
It was just an accident.

118
00:10:04,249 --> 00:10:06,546
Everything was kept private.

119
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:09,927
If anyone asks,

120
00:10:10,595 --> 00:10:14,269
tell them you and your husband were
not a good match.

121
00:10:15,939 --> 00:10:17,233
<i>Will that do?</i>

122
00:10:19,655 --> 00:10:20,741
Yes.

123
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:34,434
[chuckles]

124
00:10:50,299 --> 00:10:51,761
[in English] Are you sure it's here?

125
00:10:53,222 --> 00:10:57,773
Not a place you would think
a chemical company would be headquartered.

126
00:10:58,775 --> 00:11:00,277
So we're looking at it.

127
00:11:01,948 --> 00:11:03,660
That's the registered address.

128
00:11:03,743 --> 00:11:04,954
DESTINATION

129
00:11:12,928 --> 00:11:14,138
FOR SALE

130
00:11:27,081 --> 00:11:30,421
ASAHI BATHHOUSE

131
00:11:35,306 --> 00:11:39,063
There are several companies that
keep coming up on NPO's accounting files.

132
00:11:40,024 --> 00:11:42,403
One of the vendors
is a company called Five Winds.

133
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,575
So they're pre-vetted by the government?

134
00:11:44,658 --> 00:11:46,077
Yes, as subcontractors.

135
00:11:47,163 --> 00:11:48,332
And Five Winds?

136
00:11:48,415 --> 00:11:51,296
They received almost 500 million yen
in one year.

137
00:11:51,379 --> 00:11:53,300
500 million yen?

138
00:11:54,093 --> 00:11:55,513
An NPO with that kind of money?

139
00:11:55,597 --> 00:11:58,603
And next to the chemical company
the farmer talked about.

140
00:12:03,988 --> 00:12:04,990
Thank you.

141
00:12:06,159 --> 00:12:07,203
And there's more.

142
00:12:07,871 --> 00:12:09,040
What do you mean?

143
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:13,925
It was also the name of the gang that
my childhood friend and I made up as kids.

144
00:12:14,718 --> 00:12:17,181
Okay. So what?

145
00:12:17,264 --> 00:12:19,435
The politician, Takeuchi,

146
00:12:20,354 --> 00:12:22,149
his son was killed recently.

147
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:24,947
My family was close to theirs.

148
00:12:25,489 --> 00:12:28,412
The son, Manabu,
we were childhood friends.

149
00:12:30,290 --> 00:12:33,296
And I made up the name of the gang.
We called it Five Winds.

150
00:12:34,382 --> 00:12:35,844
You think it's related?

151
00:12:37,013 --> 00:12:38,306
That it's his company?

152
00:12:41,897 --> 00:12:42,941
Maybe.

153
00:12:43,483 --> 00:12:46,448
All right.
There's a lot of news around that.

154
00:12:48,536 --> 00:12:51,082
He tried to break up a fight at a club.

155
00:12:51,834 --> 00:12:53,629
Got killed in the brawl.

156
00:12:54,965 --> 00:12:58,346
Then his killer committed suicide
while waiting for his trial.

157
00:12:58,430 --> 00:13:00,058
And no one investigated?

158
00:13:01,645 --> 00:13:03,023
No, nothing happened.

159
00:13:42,686 --> 00:13:44,272
[Nakamura, in Japanese] Mrs. Kageyama.

160
00:13:47,571 --> 00:13:48,573
Sorry.

161
00:13:49,783 --> 00:13:51,369
I was just in the area.

162
00:13:52,413 --> 00:13:53,541
Wait.

163
00:13:59,468 --> 00:14:02,099
Please forget everything
that happened in the past.

164
00:14:03,059 --> 00:14:04,103
I know.

165
00:14:05,188 --> 00:14:06,525
It was my fault.

166
00:14:09,531 --> 00:14:11,785
I've changed since then, you know.

167
00:14:15,459 --> 00:14:18,549
I have a husband now.

168
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:20,469
I know that too.

169
00:14:23,266 --> 00:14:26,815
When I said you can come back anytime,
of course it meant working here.

170
00:14:27,859 --> 00:14:31,867
I mean it. If you want to,
I'll happily help you.

171
00:14:32,368 --> 00:14:33,913
[sighs]

172
00:14:33,996 --> 00:14:35,415
[Yumiko] Not yet.

173
00:14:36,627 --> 00:14:37,754
Because of my children.

174
00:14:38,631 --> 00:14:40,425
You were really good at your job.

175
00:14:42,471 --> 00:14:45,102
-You didn't have to quit.
-No. I did.

176
00:14:45,185 --> 00:14:46,897
Just to get married?

177
00:14:46,981 --> 00:14:48,859
That's not how you felt.

178
00:14:49,611 --> 00:14:50,655
[scoffs]

179
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,951
I was an idiot back then.

180
00:14:53,869 --> 00:14:56,709
I need to go.

181
00:14:57,209 --> 00:14:58,546
Think about it.

182
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:05,100
My husband will not like it
if I went back to my old company.

183
00:15:07,479 --> 00:15:09,776
And if you'll be my manager again,

184
00:15:10,820 --> 00:15:12,031
he'll hate it even more.

185
00:15:12,782 --> 00:15:14,035
You're right.

186
00:15:15,955 --> 00:15:18,586
I'll ask them to place you
in a different department.

187
00:15:22,176 --> 00:15:23,888
Aren't you working part-time?

188
00:15:25,265 --> 00:15:27,478
I can tell it's not just to pass the time.

189
00:15:29,649 --> 00:15:33,657
It's temporary. Until my husband
gets back on his feet--

190
00:15:33,741 --> 00:15:35,243
You should come back.

191
00:15:37,999 --> 00:15:39,961
Japan's society has changed.

192
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:44,971
I'll cooperate in making it easier
for you to return to work.

193
00:15:53,697 --> 00:15:56,995
[phone rings]

194
00:15:57,079 --> 00:15:59,876
[phone buzzes]

195
00:16:00,377 --> 00:16:01,420
[Maruyama] Yes, hello.

196
00:16:01,505 --> 00:16:03,299
[Ogami] <i>Mr. Maruyama.</i>

197
00:16:04,636 --> 00:16:06,264
Is this Mr. Ogami?

198
00:16:06,849 --> 00:16:08,936
I won't take up much of your time.

199
00:16:09,019 --> 00:16:10,272
<i>Sure.</i>

200
00:16:10,355 --> 00:16:11,567
Are you alone?

201
00:16:12,944 --> 00:16:14,739
[stammers] Please give me a moment.

202
00:16:20,918 --> 00:16:23,339
Hello? Sorry for the wait.

203
00:16:24,008 --> 00:16:25,970
<i>I know</i>

204
00:16:26,053 --> 00:16:29,728
<i>you and your brother are</i>

205
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:32,525
<i>buying votes.</i>

206
00:16:33,151 --> 00:16:35,280
I haven't done anything.

207
00:16:35,363 --> 00:16:37,911
I have no clue what my brother is doing.

208
00:16:37,994 --> 00:16:39,205
Listen carefully.

209
00:16:39,288 --> 00:16:40,457
<i>Yes.</i>

210
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:43,129
I know everything.

211
00:16:44,591 --> 00:16:47,179
<i>I won't make</i>

212
00:16:47,262 --> 00:16:48,974
<i>your vote buying public.</i>

213
00:16:50,393 --> 00:16:55,529
Your brother will plead guilty
to sexual assault.

214
00:16:56,615 --> 00:16:58,243
And that will be the end of it.

215
00:16:59,161 --> 00:17:00,163
And then?

216
00:17:00,998 --> 00:17:02,877
<i>You know very well</i>

217
00:17:02,961 --> 00:17:09,557
your faction has the prime minister's fate
in their hands.

218
00:17:10,643 --> 00:17:12,981
So what do you want me to do?

219
00:17:14,108 --> 00:17:18,742
Think about what benefits you.
Then act on it.

220
00:17:20,203 --> 00:17:21,540
In other words,

221
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:26,048
side with Secretary-General Takeuchi.

222
00:17:29,263 --> 00:17:31,183
<i>Do you understand?</i>

223
00:17:33,939 --> 00:17:35,150
Yes.

224
00:18:06,045 --> 00:18:08,341
Shin, let's clean up.

225
00:18:08,424 --> 00:18:09,511
Yeah.

226
00:18:22,244 --> 00:18:23,539
[Riko] Let's go play upstairs.

227
00:18:23,622 --> 00:18:24,666
Okay.

228
00:18:30,009 --> 00:18:32,347
I'm thinking of going back to work.

229
00:18:35,353 --> 00:18:36,439
What do you think?

230
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:40,739
Only temporarily,

231
00:18:41,616 --> 00:18:43,327
until things settle down.

232
00:18:44,539 --> 00:18:47,169
Working in finance isn't as easy
as you think.

233
00:18:48,171 --> 00:18:50,300
Shouldn't you be happy?

234
00:18:50,801 --> 00:18:51,803
Well,

235
00:18:52,304 --> 00:18:54,851
I'd be happy if it's just for you.

236
00:18:55,603 --> 00:18:58,107
But I'm the one who is responsible
for this family.

237
00:18:58,609 --> 00:19:01,238
What will I become if you start working?

238
00:19:02,365 --> 00:19:05,956
You-- Then how much longer do you need?

239
00:19:07,334 --> 00:19:08,921
A few days.

240
00:19:09,004 --> 00:19:11,050
Everything will be resolved in a week.

241
00:19:14,181 --> 00:19:16,310
Then I'll give you a week.

242
00:19:16,393 --> 00:19:17,605
-[phone buzzes]
-[sighs]

243
00:19:17,688 --> 00:19:18,774
Yeah.

244
00:19:19,651 --> 00:19:22,447
So which company were you thinking about?

245
00:19:24,577 --> 00:19:26,121
My old one.

246
00:19:27,165 --> 00:19:28,502
[chuckles] You can't.

247
00:19:28,585 --> 00:19:29,546
Why?

248
00:19:30,421 --> 00:19:33,219
There was a reason you quit.
That's why you can't go back.

249
00:19:33,302 --> 00:19:35,975
I quit because I was marrying you.

250
00:19:36,058 --> 00:19:37,352
No.

251
00:19:37,435 --> 00:19:39,273
Your boss was sexually harassing you.

252
00:19:39,356 --> 00:19:40,901
How can you even bring that up now?

253
00:19:42,487 --> 00:19:44,199
I'm going back to work for this family.

254
00:19:44,867 --> 00:19:47,707
I said that
I'm responsible for this family!

255
00:19:49,752 --> 00:19:51,506
[phone buzzes]

256
00:20:00,691 --> 00:20:03,321
Another blunder from the Watanabe Cabinet.

257
00:20:04,114 --> 00:20:07,037
Vice-Minister Hiroshi Maruyama is
receiving criticism once again

258
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:09,166
after mistakenly saying "schmooze path"

259
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:12,088
<i>instead of "smooth path"
during a press conference last week.</i>

260
00:20:12,172 --> 00:20:14,134
<i>He was already under fire
for falling asleep</i>

261
00:20:14,217 --> 00:20:19,019
<i>during a parliamentary meeting, leading
many to question his qualifications.</i>

262
00:20:19,102 --> 00:20:20,814
VICE-MINISTER MARUYAMA'S
SCHMOOZE PATH

263
00:20:43,025 --> 00:20:44,027
[door closes]

264
00:21:10,789 --> 00:21:13,002
What do you think
of the current politicians?

265
00:21:17,093 --> 00:21:20,183
We weren't like this
when we were in office.

266
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:24,609
Did I owe you any favors?

267
00:21:25,778 --> 00:21:29,577
For you to come this far to see me.

268
00:21:36,549 --> 00:21:39,429
I will have Saho divorce.

269
00:21:41,768 --> 00:21:43,103
My daughter is not…

270
00:21:45,191 --> 00:21:49,074
one of your chess pieces.

271
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:52,372
It is for her future.

272
00:21:53,792 --> 00:21:58,175
The fault lies with my son, not Saho.

273
00:22:00,514 --> 00:22:01,724
What happened?

274
00:22:03,645 --> 00:22:08,320
My son is not good enough
for your daughter.

275
00:22:09,824 --> 00:22:10,826
An affair?

276
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:16,671
A man will have one or two affairs.

277
00:22:18,508 --> 00:22:20,971
Saho only needs to grin and bear it.

278
00:22:21,681 --> 00:22:23,058
You are wrong.

279
00:22:25,104 --> 00:22:28,695
She has a right to live a happy life.

280
00:22:29,989 --> 00:22:35,458
Saho will divorce my son
and return to this house.

281
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:40,636
Even if she becomes an abandoned divorcée?

282
00:22:41,596 --> 00:22:44,810
This is the best solution.

283
00:22:45,478 --> 00:22:51,239
She will only bring shame to this family
if she returns after a second divorce.

284
00:22:53,787 --> 00:22:55,206
It is her life.

285
00:22:56,166 --> 00:22:58,128
She should decide for herself.

286
00:22:59,381 --> 00:23:02,846
Divorce is nothing special in these times.

287
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:08,566
It is different from when we were young.

288
00:23:09,359 --> 00:23:13,827
You should stop thinking
everything will go your way.

289
00:23:15,872 --> 00:23:17,918
You are a politician.

290
00:23:18,712 --> 00:23:21,383
A well-respected politician
with a good reputation.

291
00:23:23,555 --> 00:23:26,393
I live in the shadows,

292
00:23:26,476 --> 00:23:29,900
never stepping into the light.

293
00:23:30,777 --> 00:23:36,288
Not a single soul knows who I am,
or who my family are.

294
00:23:39,002 --> 00:23:40,004
So?

295
00:23:41,632 --> 00:23:47,268
It will only hurt you and your family
if she stays in this marriage.

296
00:23:49,064 --> 00:23:53,489
Ending it quickly is for Saho's sake.

297
00:23:56,286 --> 00:23:57,330
No.

298
00:23:59,502 --> 00:24:01,088
It's all for you.

299
00:24:17,411 --> 00:24:18,540
[sighs]

300
00:24:25,554 --> 00:24:26,848
[phone ringing]

301
00:24:30,479 --> 00:24:31,691
WATARU MGR

302
00:24:35,281 --> 00:24:36,324
[Wataru] <i>Hello?</i>

303
00:24:36,408 --> 00:24:39,915
If it's that photo you asked for,
I'll send it to you later.

304
00:24:40,416 --> 00:24:43,380
I can't even put on my lipstick
properly right now.

305
00:24:43,463 --> 00:24:45,927
<i>A car will pick you up in an hour.</i>

306
00:24:46,846 --> 00:24:48,808
Okay. I'll be ready.

307
00:24:49,392 --> 00:24:50,687
You'll have a rehearsal, right?

308
00:24:51,396 --> 00:24:54,277
Ken will start by introducing
you to the audience.

309
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:57,283
And the event will take about an hour.

310
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:58,912
<i>Okay.</i>

311
00:24:59,454 --> 00:25:01,041
After that will be your song.

312
00:25:01,792 --> 00:25:02,836
<i>I know.</i>

313
00:25:03,630 --> 00:25:06,552
<i>Break a leg. It's a big opportunity.</i>

314
00:25:07,638 --> 00:25:10,476
I know. I'll do well.

315
00:25:12,188 --> 00:25:14,234
<i>Where will your boyfriend be tonight?</i>

316
00:25:16,363 --> 00:25:19,452
Well, I invited him.

317
00:25:20,162 --> 00:25:21,540
I knew it.

318
00:25:22,584 --> 00:25:23,586
Don't.

319
00:25:24,420 --> 00:25:26,174
I want him to see me.

320
00:25:26,258 --> 00:25:28,136
He's only going to watch me sing.

321
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:29,264
<i>Damn it.</i>

322
00:25:29,347 --> 00:25:31,519
Doing whatever you want.

323
00:25:33,063 --> 00:25:36,236
Then never say a word about
you dating him.

324
00:25:36,319 --> 00:25:38,198
<i>He'll only stand there and watch.</i>

325
00:25:38,282 --> 00:25:41,121
<i>Don't even talk to him. Don't go near him.</i>

326
00:25:41,789 --> 00:25:43,458
That's my prerogative.

327
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:45,505
I'll see you later.

328
00:25:51,182 --> 00:25:52,686
Just stand there and watch?

329
00:25:54,230 --> 00:25:55,232
Ignore him.

330
00:25:57,863 --> 00:25:59,825
Are we in a prison?

331
00:26:00,744 --> 00:26:01,996
Is this what your dream is?

332
00:26:02,956 --> 00:26:04,627
You can just ignore it.

333
00:26:06,046 --> 00:26:09,928
Look, I don't want
to fight with you over this.

334
00:26:10,847 --> 00:26:11,932
Go and sing.

335
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:13,477
I'll stay home.

336
00:26:15,982 --> 00:26:18,655
I don't want to get involved
in these petty things.

337
00:26:20,617 --> 00:26:22,746
But I want you to be there.

338
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,921
You don't have a choice, do you?

339
00:26:29,217 --> 00:26:30,302
No.

340
00:26:33,225 --> 00:26:34,645
I make my own decisions.

341
00:26:37,901 --> 00:26:38,945
Okay.

342
00:26:45,249 --> 00:26:47,086
I need to finish my makeup.

343
00:26:48,548 --> 00:26:51,052
And send my manager that petty photo.

344
00:27:05,080 --> 00:27:07,501
[photographer] Get closer.
[in English] Three, two, one.

345
00:27:13,890 --> 00:27:14,892
Risako.

346
00:27:19,902 --> 00:27:21,614
[in Japanese]
He's from the marketing agency.

347
00:27:22,114 --> 00:27:23,618
-Smile. Smile.
-Okay.

348
00:27:25,370 --> 00:27:26,372
Pardon me.

349
00:27:27,082 --> 00:27:28,920
This is our newest singer, Risako Ogami.

350
00:27:29,003 --> 00:27:30,339
I'm Risako Ogami.

351
00:27:31,424 --> 00:27:32,969
She will be singing tonight.

352
00:27:33,053 --> 00:27:34,138
-I can't wait.
-Me neither.

353
00:27:34,222 --> 00:27:35,934
-I'd love to see it.
-I'll do my best.

354
00:27:36,017 --> 00:27:37,186
-Good luck.
-Thank you.

355
00:27:39,608 --> 00:27:40,735
Ken is here.

356
00:27:45,452 --> 00:27:47,206
Congratulations.

357
00:27:47,289 --> 00:27:48,458
Wow!

358
00:27:48,543 --> 00:27:50,420
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

359
00:27:50,505 --> 00:27:52,091
-Thank you.
-Did you meet Mr. Sato?

360
00:27:52,592 --> 00:27:53,803
No? Not yet?

361
00:27:53,886 --> 00:27:55,097
-Go say hi first.
-Okay.

362
00:27:56,934 --> 00:27:58,938
Long time no see, Mr. Sato.

363
00:27:59,021 --> 00:28:01,025
-Thank you for coming today.
-Not at all.

364
00:28:01,527 --> 00:28:03,154
This is Risako Ogami.

365
00:28:03,656 --> 00:28:06,620
She's making her debut soon.
She's going to be a big hit.

366
00:28:06,704 --> 00:28:07,872
Nice to meet you.

367
00:28:08,749 --> 00:28:13,133
Mr. Sato is the vice president of
Muse Music. He's a legend in the industry.

368
00:28:13,968 --> 00:28:15,304
No, you're exaggerating.

369
00:28:15,387 --> 00:28:16,431
Don't be so humble.

370
00:28:16,515 --> 00:28:18,018
[people clamoring]

371
00:28:18,101 --> 00:28:19,980
-[person] She's so pretty.
-[people clamoring]

372
00:28:24,363 --> 00:28:27,036
-Mr. Sato!
-Sheena.

373
00:28:27,537 --> 00:28:30,585
How long has it been?
I'm so happy to see you.

374
00:28:30,668 --> 00:28:31,920
Good to see you're well.

375
00:28:32,004 --> 00:28:34,258
You too, Mr. Sato. I'll talk to you later.

376
00:28:38,308 --> 00:28:40,228
I'm happy to see you too.

377
00:28:41,064 --> 00:28:42,609
Honey, you look gorgeous.

378
00:28:43,151 --> 00:28:45,698
Didn't I say that dress is perfect?

379
00:28:45,782 --> 00:28:48,161
Yes, thank you so much.

380
00:28:49,121 --> 00:28:52,211
You surprised me.
I didn't know you were coming.

381
00:28:53,129 --> 00:28:56,177
I can't miss such an important day.

382
00:28:56,804 --> 00:28:58,516
And? What will you sing?

383
00:28:59,643 --> 00:29:02,607
The song Ken wrote for me.
We're debuting it here.

384
00:29:03,233 --> 00:29:04,569
Really?

385
00:29:05,278 --> 00:29:07,282
Even though you could sing your own song?

386
00:29:09,579 --> 00:29:11,667
Ken is the one who chooses the song.

387
00:29:16,719 --> 00:29:19,683
Don't you want to sing the song you wrote?

388
00:29:22,856 --> 00:29:24,108
Of course I do.

389
00:29:25,068 --> 00:29:26,655
If it's okay with Ken.

390
00:29:27,406 --> 00:29:28,491
Okay.

391
00:29:29,995 --> 00:29:31,330
I'll try to talk to him.

392
00:29:35,297 --> 00:29:37,594
CONGRATULATIONS
RISAKO OGAMI - SHEENA

393
00:29:38,763 --> 00:29:41,350
Risako, did you hear you're

394
00:29:41,894 --> 00:29:44,273
-…singing your song?
-Really?

395
00:29:44,356 --> 00:29:45,818
That's what I was told.

396
00:29:46,444 --> 00:29:47,488
What happened?

397
00:29:48,824 --> 00:29:50,745
Sheena did it.

398
00:29:50,828 --> 00:29:51,872
[laughs]

399
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,130
Will you be okay?

400
00:29:57,759 --> 00:29:58,803
Yes.

401
00:30:06,777 --> 00:30:09,114
[person 1] Mic check. Mic check.

402
00:30:12,371 --> 00:30:14,751
[person 2] It's taking too long.

403
00:30:24,186 --> 00:30:25,272
Sheena.

404
00:30:26,817 --> 00:30:28,444
Why did you do that?

405
00:30:29,573 --> 00:30:33,998
It's a good song.
This will be good for her.

406
00:30:34,081 --> 00:30:36,127
But it's not her debut song.

407
00:30:45,897 --> 00:30:50,698
There's no need to be scared
even if she is more talented than you.

408
00:30:51,324 --> 00:30:53,662
It could just be beginner's luck.

409
00:30:57,795 --> 00:30:58,881
I don't get it.

410
00:31:00,635 --> 00:31:01,845
It's fine.

411
00:31:03,682 --> 00:31:07,565
Be sure to give your new singer
a good introduction.

412
00:31:08,609 --> 00:31:09,653
Okay?

413
00:31:22,344 --> 00:31:23,889
[in English] Ladies and gentlemen.

414
00:31:25,768 --> 00:31:30,485
[in Japanese] I am very happy to introduce
a wonderful artist to you tonight.

415
00:31:30,569 --> 00:31:32,406
[audience clapping]

416
00:31:33,241 --> 00:31:37,583
She will mesmerize you
with her beautiful voice.

417
00:31:37,667 --> 00:31:42,009
Making her debut tonight
singing an original song, <i>RISE</i>,

418
00:31:42,092 --> 00:31:44,221
is Risako Ogami.

419
00:32:00,546 --> 00:32:03,468
♪ <i>You know sometimes
I wish you'd scream at me</i> ♪

420
00:32:04,470 --> 00:32:07,309
♪ <i>Have a fit
And throw your clothes on me</i> ♪

421
00:32:08,144 --> 00:32:10,941
♪ <i>Be inconsiderate and ignore me</i> ♪

422
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:14,991
♪ <i>Or just laugh along and smile with me</i> ♪

423
00:32:15,785 --> 00:32:18,206
♪ <i>Show me your face so I can read better</i> ♪

424
00:32:19,500 --> 00:32:22,380
♪ <i>And know exactly
What you're thinking, yeah</i> ♪

425
00:32:23,299 --> 00:32:26,472
♪ <i>Cause I'm exhausted
Trying to impress you</i> ♪

426
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:30,146
♪ <i>Even though I know I don't have to</i> ♪

427
00:32:31,566 --> 00:32:33,402
♪ <i>Baby</i> ♪

428
00:32:33,486 --> 00:32:37,954
♪ <i>Every little thing I do
Is just for you</i> ♪

429
00:32:38,037 --> 00:32:41,795
♪ <i>I wanna see a rise yeah</i> ♪

430
00:32:41,878 --> 00:32:45,176
♪ <i>So open up your eyes yeah</i> ♪

431
00:32:46,596 --> 00:32:48,432
♪ <i>And baby</i> ♪

432
00:32:48,517 --> 00:32:53,234
♪ <i>I hope it makes me want you
More than yesterday</i> ♪

433
00:32:53,317 --> 00:32:56,575
♪ <i>So tell me do you like yeah</i> ♪

434
00:32:57,117 --> 00:33:00,791
♪ <i>Can't read between the lines yeah</i> ♪

